# Keep the Docker build context (and the resulting server image) lean.
# The Dockerfile does `COPY . .` then `go build`; the Go binary needs only
# source. Without this, the context pulled in the multi-GB hermetic engine
# bundle, the SQLite DB, and build artifacts → an 18 GB image + disk-fill.
#
# (server-web owns the Dockerfile — added by transcription after a build filled
#  /home; sanity-check nothing here is needed at image-build time. Runtime data
#  is volume-mounted, not baked in.)

# Hermetic ML engine bundle + its build cache (#55/#57) — never needed in the image
engine/dist/
engine/.build-cache/
engine/.validate/

# Runtime data — mounted as a volume at runtime, must not be baked in
data/
generated/
library/
# testdata/ is multi-GB (PJ's live library lives under testdata/library); the
# server image needs none of it (tests use it, the Dockerfile only builds).
testdata/

# Build artifacts
bin/
**/__pycache__/
*.test

# Node / web tooling (web UI is committed pre-built + go:embed'd from internal/)
node_modules/

# VCS / local
.git/
.gitignore
